  "prompt": "What do I do when I have a feeling my live-in girlfriend is cheating on me?",
  "response": "Here are some steps you might consider:\n\n1. Communicate openly\n- Talk to her directly about your concerns\n- Be calm and non-accusatory\n- Listen to her explanation\n\n2. Look for potential signs\n- Changes in behavior or routine\n- Increased privacy with phone/computer\n- Emotional distance\n- Unexplained absences\n\n3. Gather evidence (carefully)\n- Don't invade her privacy illegally\n- Avoid stalking or extreme behavior\n- Focus on concrete facts\n\n4. Trust your instincts\n- If something feels consistently wrong, there might be an issue\n\n5. Consider relationship counseling\n- Can help improve communication\n- Provides neutral ground to discuss concerns\n\n6. Be prepared for different outcomes\n- Decide what you're willing to accept\n- Know your personal boundaries\n\n7. Take care of yourself\n- Seek support from friends/family\n- Manage your emotional health\n- Don't let suspicions consume you\n\n8. If cheating is confirmed\n- Decide whether you want to work on the relationship\n- Or choose to end it\n\nRemember, these are general suggestions. Each situation is unique, and what works best depends on your specific circumstances.\n\nWould you like to discuss this further?",
